text: Daleville is a city in Dale County of Alabama in the United States. At the 2020 census, 4,866 people lived there. It is part of the Ozark Micropolitan Statistical Area. The city's nickname is "Gateway to Fort Rucker", as this U.S. Army post is just north of town. Cairns Army Airfield is to the south of Daleville on the road to nearly Clayhatchee. ==Notable residents of Daleville== *Mickey Andrews – College football coach *Tony Richardson – NFL player *Robert W.
